review_blob: Decent Tripel, but nothing to write home about. A little too sweet. Hops is too prevelent. More like a sweet  hoppy ale.
This beer has a lot of character for a porter. Cofee, chocholate, malt, and hops are all present in a nice combination. Cant wait to try their RIS.
Eh, pretty good beer. This is not really my style of beer so I may rerate eventually.
Eh, pretty good beer. This is not really my style of beer so I may rerate eventually.

Fairly good belgian ale. Alcohol is hidden mainly by lots of sweet flavors. I tend to prefer the dry belgians but this is still pretty good. Comparable to Three Floyds Alpha Kong IMO, taste wise at least.
High quality coffee beans are present in this brew and they are preseneted in an unburnt fashion. This has been my favorite straight up java stout.
beer_name: Southern Tier Jah-va Imperial Coffee Stout

review_blob: This beer was just a little too much. Too sweet and too much alcohol. The alcohol is hidden well because of the suger, but you sure do feel it after finishing off a bomber.
Quality stout from the Japanese. I wasnt a huge fan of this particular coffee flavor, but its still good.
If you like chocholate you will "double" like this beer. Chocholate + stout = mmmmmmmmmm
Overall rating is spot on. This is a great beer for those breaking into good beers.
Good solid stout. Bells doesnt dissapoint. Quality coffee + stout = mmmmmmmmm
Lots of flavor for a dry stout. Im really starting to enjoy a little bit of sour in some of my stouts. Gotta love the value of dark horse beers.
Overall ranking is dead on with this one. A great next step after guiness for those breaking into the good stuff.
Another great belgian. Ranks slightly behind St Bernardus and Rochy 10 in my book, but still quite good.
Very drinkable for a dark beer. Not great, but would still be a good choice for someone breaking into craft brews. Step after guiness perhaps.
Solid very drinkable stout. Id compare this to any of the bells stouts besides expedition. Good flavor, fair price, and you can drink it all night
Im not a huge IPA fan, but this was a drinkable beer along with the 60 minute. Will probably enjoy it more in the future. May rerate.
A quality brew. I wouldnt but it in my heavy hitter category for stouts, but at least it doesnt have the generic hoppy bitterness many average (in my book) stouts have. This one passes

Overpowering chocholate. This one is almost to the point that I wouldnt call it beer. However, the chocholate is of high quality, and the brew is tasty so it gets good marks. Tastes good and gets you drunk.

I group this in my collection of average imperial stouts, which contains 75% of them. It has its pluses and minuses, blah blah blah. Expected more from a rogue beer in a fancy ceramic bottle and a hefty price tag.
Another good beer from rogue. A good begineers stout. Decent amount of flavor. Quite tasty
Another good beer from rogue. A good begineers stout. Decent amount of flavor. Quite tasty
Right up there with St. Bernardus 12 as my two favorite belgian brews. Cant wait to try a westy
UPDATED: MAR 24, 2008

Ya, I know. This beer is a badass. Not only does it contain every ingrediant under the sun, and maybe some from the underworld, that I enjoy in a stout, but it seems like I can pick out any flavor I want at any time or just let them all blend together to make a fine brew. Like the wizard of beers all I say is, "there is no thing like a cherry stout" and I take a sip. Bam, a top notch cherry stout flavor. Can do that with so many flavors its unbelievable. Fantastic beer. I would say it is worth the hype, but there is no hype over this beer, just fact.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Very complex flavor, yet very balanced. Id like it to have a little more hitting power when having imperial stout AND Boris the Crusher in its name, but I wont hold it against this beer.
Quality brew. very nice use of chocholate. Bitterness lowers it a few points for me, but it wasnt too bitter where I couldnt detect the positive flavors.
beer_name: Thirsty Dog Siberian Night Imperial Stout

review_blob: UPDATED: MAR 20, 2008

The beer was decent. The flavor was a little artificial and the chocolate and cherry tastes were not that enjoyable. However, the aroma gave me smell memories to past Halloweens and I spent most of the time trying to figure out a certain flavor that this beer reminded me of. The closest I could get on one bottle was double bubble gum or the gum that used to come with baseball cards. May have to buy more to in narrow down the flavor some more.
Very nice light and refreshing beer. Oranges present on every sip, but no overpowering. If I were to have a beer for breakfast, this would be near the top of the list.

Not much to say about this one and I think they want it that way. Its not an imperial , dry, or sweet stout. Its just a stout. Well balanced with a good amount of flavor for a 6% brew. Drink all night with no regrets. Fine Bells product.

Im starting to enjoy IPAs a little bit more and even will choose dreadnaught or dogfish 90 minute over a good stout on some nights. However, this beer was a challenge to drink. I found it to have only 1 dimension, hops. Not balanced.

Probably my least favorite Three Floyds beverage Ive had to date. Too much going on for a dry stout. Looks like they were trying to make a beer with a  little bit of something for everyone and ending up with an average beer.
UPDATED: MAR 20, 2008
Tasty Beverage. This one goes right up there with Guinness. May even have a little more flavor.
Pretty thin beer. I prefer Guinness and murphys. Probably will not buy this one again.
Lots of flavor and decent thickness for not being a an imperial stout. Sweet coffee. Good beer.
Pretty thin and not too much flavor. Coffee and malt.  Decent beer, but wont buy again.

The fact that this used to be my top tier beer makes me twinge a little. However, its still one of the best beer you can find a lot of local liquor stores. Decent amount of flavor, pretty unique, and drinkable
This beer really does speak for itself. It is an okay beer. Wouldnt turn one down
My favorite light beer, even though that isnt saying much. If I ever went on a diet, this beer gives a good reason to not give up beer altogether. No other light beer can say that much in my book.
My staple beer along with MGD for a long time. I think Bud has a little more of a distinct flavor though. Refreshing. Anheuser-Busch would still have my respect if this is the only beer they made.
My staple beer, along with bud for a long time. Refreshing. Good price. Doesnt taste bad and will eventually get you drunk.
